ProtoDefines:
. "Let $p$ be an odd prime and let $a$ be an integer. Set{p} 
   )$|nn} $$ (\frac{a}{p} ) = \begin{cases} 0 & if $\gcd(a,p) 
   \neq 1$,\\ +1 & if $a$ is a quadratic residue, and\\ -1 & if
   $a$ is a quadratic nonresidue. \end{cases} $$ We call this 
   symbol the Legendre Symbol."
